            Claire Gonzales
          
          
            
              I am a PhD student studying the co-location of aquaculture systems with renewable energy in the marine environment. I conduct this research as part of the Froehlich Laboratory at the University of California, Santa Barbara. In my free time, I am happiest in the water, on the trail, or drinking coffee somewhere.
